com.outbrain.aletheia.datum

Class InMemoryEndPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.outbrain.aletheia.datum.InMemoryEndPoint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConsumptionEndPoint, DatumKeyAwareFetchEndPoint<byte[]>, FetchConsumptionEndPoint<byte[]>, EndPoint, Named, DatumKeyAwareNamedSender<byte[]>, DatumKeyAwareSender<byte[]>, NamedSender<byte[]>, ProductionEndPoint, Sender<byte[]>, Serializable, AutoCloseable

    public class InMemoryEndPoint
extends Object
implements ProductionEndPoint, FetchConsumptionEndPoint<byte[]>, DatumKeyAwareNamedSender<byte[]>, NamedSender<byte[]>, DatumKeyAwareFetchEndPoint<byte[]>, Serializable
    A special kind of EndPoint that allows clients to construct a pipeline where the DatumProducer produces into an in-memory end point and the DatumConsumerStream consumes data off of it. This type of endpoint is useful for in-memory experiments and tests, and can simulate a quasi-synchronous, blocking produce/consume model if it's created with size = 1. Deliver with callback api is not suppoted in this implementation, callbacks will be ignored.
